==Definition==

<b>hemisphere</b> (<i>noun</i>), plural <b>hemispheres</b>
# (<i>geometry</i>) A half-[[sphere]], formed by a [[plane]] intersecting the center of a sphere.
# (<i>generally</i>) A half-sphere, formed by a plane intersecting the centre of an approximately [[spherical]] body.
# (<i>geography</i>) Half of the [[earth]], the [[Northern Hemisphere]], [[Southern Hemisphere]], [[Western Hemisphere]] or [[Eastern Hemisphere]].

